DataElement.preferredName: Dimension Multiple Point Frame of Reference Unique Identifier ISO21090.II.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The spatial outline of an object as described by the configuration of straight or curved lines.:Having, relating to, or consisting of more than one individual, element, part, or other component; manifold. (dictionary.com):The precise location of something; a spatially limited location._A set of ideas, as of philosophical or religious doctrine, in terms of which other ideas are interpreted or assigned meaning; a system that uses coordinates to establish position.:A set of characters used as a code that is unique in the context or the system for which it is created. It serves as a means of identification and reference (often instead of a name) for an entity, person, thing, function, procedure, activity, variable, or body of data._Identifier that uniquely identifies a thing or object.
